misc: Moved with his family from Rochester, NY to Washington, DC in autumn 1865.  Served with the 7th Cavalry in the Sioux campaign, winter 1890/91, in SD; was in the Battle of Wounded Knee near Pine Ridge.  On duty with Indians at Ft. Sill, Oklahoma Territory, for 5 years except for 6 months with troops on the Rio Grande in pursuit of Garcia.  Served on Maj. Gen. Miles's staff during the Chicago riots of 1894.  Stationed at Ft. Myer, VA, Nov. 1898 to Jan. 1899.  In the Spanish American War, served at Chickamauga and Lexington, afterward on Gen. Wilson's staff at Matanzas, Cuba, in relief work for the reconcentrados.  Served in the Philippines, notably with a regiment at Batangas, Luzon.
